<HEADLINE>
ERSTAD`S DRY SPELL CONTINUES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 c.1999 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. _ Last season Darin Erstad hit .316 with 17
homers and 57 RBI by the end of June. As of Sunday he was hitting
.243 with three homers and 12 RBI.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's just trying to get some timing, stay inside the ball, all
those things you talk about,'' Anaheim Angels manager Terry Collins
said. ``Every time you're in a slump, you ask where are my hands,
where are my feet? Once in a while you need to take the approach of
going in the batter's box, see the ball, hit it. And work on the
little things. When you're a good hitter and you're not swinging
good, it's rough.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Moving swiftly along: The Angels barely had enough time to do
their laundry after returning early Friday morning from a 10-day
trip to the East Coast before returning East again.
</P>
<P>
   They leave this morning for a seven-day, six-game trip to
Baltimore and Tampa.
</P>
<P>
   ``They say everybody's got to do it,'' Collins said of the
hectic travel schedule. ``But that doesn't make it right.
</P>
<P>
   These three games against Tampa Bay were the Angels' only home
dates in an 18-game stretch.
</P>
<P>
   __ Greene back behind plate: Todd Greene completed his
three-game suspension Saturday and started at catcher Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   Greene, who was suspended for three days for charging Mariners
pitcher Brett Hinchliffe in a game April 18, will get some starts
in the outfield on the upcoming trip. Sunday, for the first time
since shoulder surgery, he threw out a baserunner trying to steal.
Four others have stolen successfully on him this season.
</P>
<P>
   __ Schedule: The Angels are off today. They begin a three-game
series against the Baltimore Orioles at Camden Yards on Tuesday.
Chuck Finley (2-3, 4.89 ERA) will start for Anaheim against
Baltimore's Mike Mussina (5-1, 4.89).
</P>
<P>
   __ Also: Anaheim's Dave Silvestri, a 31-year-old utilityman,
made his first career outfield start in left field. Silvestri had
made five previous outfield appearances, the last on May 21, 1996,
with the Montreal Expos.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
