<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Claris Home Page offers clear, easy program
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ With Claris Home Page, making a Web site is as easy as
designing a flier or newsletter with a word processor.
</P>
<P>
   The program successfully hides and automates all the cumbersome
encoding involved in making Internet documents. All the user has to
worry about is design.
</P>
<P>
   And, if you're not particularly good at design, the program
comes with lots of templates. You can either fill them in with your
own information or change the templates as you see fit.
</P>
<P>
   Home Page, though, is not just for novices. The program will let
advanced users see and edit the HTML code that controls Web pages.
</P>
<P>
   Whether you're a novice or expert, you'll find Home Page easy to
navigate, fast and responsive. It works, in short, in the tradition
of most Claris products.
</P>
<P>
   Actually, Claris no longer exists. Apple Computer spun it off
last year. The company is now called FileMaker Pro, and Home Page
has been redesigned to work seamlessly with the database program of
the same name. More on that later.
</P>
<P>
   When you fire up Home Page, what you see is the standard empty
document window of a word processor. There is a difference, though.
</P>
<P>
   The toolbar that tops the page sports buttons related to
creating a Web page. There's a button for creating hyperlinks to
other files and Web pages. Other buttons let you add tables and
frames that a Web browser can read.
</P>
<P>
   These buttons are part of Home Page's graphical approach to Web
design. What you see on your screen is pretty much, although not
exactly, how your page will look on the Net.
</P>
<P>
   To see exactly how your page will look, Home Page lets you test
it live in either of the two major browsers. There's a button for
that in the toolbar. Testing a design is important, because the
look of a page can differ among browsers.
</P>
<P>
   One of the coolest tricks of Home Page is its ability to use a
database created by FileMaker Pro 4.0. Home Page does it through a
feature called FileMaker Pro Connection Assistant. For it to work,
FileMaker Pro must be installed on the server that houses your Web
page.
</P>
<P>
   Home Page is much more than a page designer. The program also
includes tools that let you manage your site. These, too, are easy
to understand and operate.
</P>
<P>
   Home Page retails for about $100. You can download a free 30-day
trial of the program from the FileMaker Web site at
www.filemaker.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
