</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Get ready to . . . giggle
 &HT;    By Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   Do you think your giggle's got what it takes? The Pillsbury
Doughboy will be the judge of that in this year's Giggle-Off
Contest. Call 1-888-WE-GIGGLE (934-4453) before May 31 and leave
your best hardee-har-har on the recorder. (Don't try to imitate the
Doughboy. Leave your own outrageous laugh.) Ten finalists will be
chosen to win a three-day trip to Los Angeles to compete in a live
giggle competition in October. Besides being named America's Best
Giggler, the winner will take home $50,000. Last year's champ was a
7-year-old girl.
</P>
<P>
   Don't touch that dial!
</P>
<P>
   If you've ever dreamed of hosting your own radio show, here's
your chance to prove your stuff. Host Michael Feldman is looking
for a kid 16 or under to take over his public radio show ``Whad 'Ya
Know?'' for a day. Replacements will be picked for the host, the
announcer and the two jazz musicians. The show will fly you to the
studios June 24, and you'll be on live June 26. All you have to do
is send a five-minute audition tape by June 4 to Whad 'Ya Know: The
Next Generation, 821 University Ave., Madison, WI 53706. To find a
station close to you, check out www.notmuch.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
