<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-TOOLS18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Design Shop builds Web sites well
 &HT;    By Jack Warner
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Anyone wishing to make a no-holds-barred Web site
without learning HTML code ought to consider investing in a program
called Internet/Intranet Design Shop Gold.
</P>
<P>
   You're going to have to invest in something if you want a
what-you-see-is-what-you-get Web site builder, and Design Shop is
the best I've seen. It not only does the job, it comes with just
about all the bells and whistles you'd want to add to your site.
</P>
<P>
   As a sort of by-the-way feature, it will also do posters,
banners, certificates and calendars for printing on paper.
</P>
<P>
   Because Design Shop is powerful, one needs to go through the
tutorial and keep the manual close at hand for a while. It's not
really a difficult program to use, but its many features lead to
complications.
</P>
<P>
   Somewhat like Microsoft's Front Page, it provides various views
of the Web site being created, all of them selected from a screen
called the Site Manager.
</P>
<P>
   The Physical Layout view presents the site in a tree-like
structure. Most of the work will be done from the Logical Layout,
which presents each page with its relationship to others. The
Navigate Layout screen shows all connections, chiefly to let the
user hunt for any missing or broken links.
</P>
<P>
   There are controls that make it simple to keep a standard look
from page to page in the site, but these controls are also easily
overridden if you want to get crazy.
</P>
<P>
   Creating frames is quite simple, and you can stuff a bunch of
them on a page if you wish. Tables are also easy to handle, and can
be expanded to cover an entire page and used to keep bulleted items
in order. As in a word processor, standard headers and footers can
be created and the program will place them on each page.
</P>
<P>
   Design Shop comes with 45,000 images, sound clips, videos and
animations that can be used in a Web site; there is also a powerful
graphics editor and 25 separate types of business charts. There are
a bunch of templates _ basically, ready-made items _ for every
function of the program, including Web sites. Good for those who
want to do something, but don't know what or even why.
</P>
<P>
   A one-button click gives you a preview of any page at any time.
</P>
<P>
   I tried hard to find something to carp about here, and all I
could come up with concerns the icons on the multitude of menu
bars. They are rather obscure and unintuitive. So there.
</P>
<P>
   Internet/Intranet Design Shop Gold is made by Boomerang
Software, and it retails for $139. It ought to be generally
available, but if you can't find it at a store, go to the Web site
www.boomerangsoftware.com.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
