<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NFK-FEATURE-PHANTOMENACE18-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A new generation of kids will get to consider good vs. evil
 &HT;    By Doug Hamilton
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Along time ago, in a decade far, far away _ the 1970s!
_ kids the same age as you lined up for a new movie called ``Star
Wars.'' At the time, few probably thought the fantasy film they
were waiting to see would become one of the most popular movies
ever.
</P>
<P>
   Kids around the world loved ``Star Wars'' and its sequels, ``The
Empire Strikes Back'' and ``Return of the Jedi.'' The movies had it
all: good guys to root for, bad guys to boo, exciting battles,
monsters, funny sidekicks and even a beautiful princess. The world
created on-screen seemed like nothing we'd ever experienced.
</P>
<P>
   Actually, ``Star Wars'' tells a very old story, but in a new
way. We see variations on the series' characters in everything from
the centuries-old legend of King Arthur and his Knights of the
Round Table to fairy tales and even Disney movies.
</P>
<P>
   On Wednesday, a new generation of kids will flock to theaters to
see the ``prequel'' to ``Star Wars,'' called ``Star Wars: Episode I
_ The Phantom Menace.'' (Prequel means that the action takes place
before the time shown in the original movie.)
</P>
<P>
   So, what characters will return from ``Star Wars'' and who will
be new? We've provided a list. See if you can find similar
characters in other stories. Who are the good guys, or heroes, in
the legend of King Arthur? Who is the bad guy, or villain, in the
story of Peter Pan? Who are the funny sidekicks in ``Alice in
Wonderland''?
</P>
<P>
   If nothing else, it'll give you something to think about while
you're waiting in line for ``The Phantom Menace.''
</P>
<P>
   THE HEROES
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars''
</P>
<P>
   _ Luke Skywalker _ A young farmhand on the planet of Tatooine
who joins the Rebel Alliance to fight the Evil Empire.
</P>
<P>
   _ Han Solo _ A smuggler and pilot of the Millennium Falcon. He
helps Luke Skywalker and Princess Leia battle the Evil Empire.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   _ Obi-Wan Kenobi _ Jedi Knight and mentor to Anakin Skywalker,
who later joins the Dark Side and becomes Darth Vader.
</P>
<P>
   _ Qui-Gon Jinn _ A Jedi Master who travels the galaxy protecting
citizens of the Republic.
</P>
<P>
   THE VILLAINS
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars''
</P>
<P>
   _ Darth Vader _ Robed in black, his head covered by a scary
helmet and face mask, Darth Vader is one of the most feared leaders
of the Empire.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   _ Darth Maul _ His face has ugly black and red marks. He fights
with a double-sided light saber, and he's out to get Qui-Gon Jinn
and Obi-Wan Kenobi.
</P>
<P>
   THE ROYAL LADIES
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars''
</P>
<P>
   _ Princess Leia _ One of the galaxy's most respected leaders,
Leia aids the rebels in fighting the Empire. But Darth Vader orders
her capture.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   _ Queen Amidala _ As leader of the planet Naboo, Amidala risks
her life to save her people when evil forces launch an invasion.
</P>
<P>
   THE SIDEKICKS
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars''
</P>
<P>
   _ R2D2 and C-3PO _ The bickering ``droids'' get into all sorts
of scrapes as they accompany Luke Skywalker in battle.
</P>
<P>
   _ Chewbacca _ Han Solo's furry Wookie friend.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   _ Jar Jar Binks _ A very clumsy alien who latches onto the brave
Qui-Gon Jinn. The odd Jar Jar looks a little bit like a walking
iguana.
</P>
<P>
   MONSTERS
</P>
<P>
   ``Star Wars''
</P>
<P>
   In the original movie, savage Sand People prowled the deserts of
Tatooine and a mysterious slimy thing almost killed Luke Skywalker
in the Death Star's trash compactor. ``Return of the Jedi''
introduced the blobby Jabba the Hutt and his horrible pet Rancor.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Phantom Menace''
</P>
<P>
   Expect to see giant, space-ship eating fish and several
dinosaur-like creatures.
</P>
<P>
   OTHER NAMES TO KNOW IN ``THE PHANTOM MENACE''
</P>
<P>
   Remember all the weird names in ``Star Wars?'' Luke Skywalker's
home planet was called Tatooine, but there's no planet by that name
in our solar system. Hans Solo visited the dangerous city of Mos
Eisley, but you won't find that name on any map.
</P>
<P>
   These names were made up by the people who made ``Star Wars'' to
describe the fantasy world they created. More new phrases pop up in
``The Phantom Menace.'' Here are a few you need to know:
</P>
<P>
   Coruscant: A skyscraper-covered world that serves as the center
of power for the Old Republic. Corscant is home to the headquarters
of the Jedi Knights.
</P>
<P>
   Naboo: This small, green planet is inhabited by two advanced
civilizations along with many exotic creatures, including the Nuna,
which looks like a cross between a turky and a frog.
</P>
<P>
   Theed: The capital of Naboo, site of the beautiful Theed Palace,
where Queen Amidala lives.
</P>
<P>
   The Galactic Senate: The ruling body of the Republic. More than
a thousand senators from all over the galaxy gather in the Main
Senate Chamber on Coruscant to discuss problems and pass laws.
</P>
<P>
   Mos Espa: A spaceport on the dry, dusty planet of Tatooine, it
is the home of young Anakin Skywalker (later Darth Vader).
</P>
<P>
   Naboo Royal N-1 Starfighter: A sleek spaceship designed for use
by Queen Amidala's Honor Guard on patrols and escort missions.
</P>
<P>
   The Gungans: A race of lizard-like beings on Naboo that lend
Obi-Wan Kenobi and Qui-Gon Jinn a space vessel to help fight
invaders.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
