<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-MENACE _ Is George Lucas' new movie visually amazing?
Yes. Exciting? Sometimes. Emotionally involving? Almost never. As a
technological Everest (and the Mt. McKinley of marketing),
``Menace'' is a remarkable achievement. Too bad writer-director
Lucas left out the gee-whiz enthusiasm of the original movies. He
also left out memorable characters. He left out the fun. Should you
see it? Sure, you have to. It's a worldwide phenomenon. (Murray,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   NEWSSTAND _ Periodicals on the newsstands this week. (O'Briant,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
