<P>
   Noticed all the baby strollers in your neighborhood?
</P>
<P>
   You're witnessing an echo of the Baby Boom. Those babies and
their parents, your readers, need advice and support _ and they can
get it every week from  &UR; Dr. T. Berry Brazelton, America's most
respected pediatrician and longtime columnist for The New York
Times Syndicate. &LR;
</P>
<P>
   In ``Families Today,'' which comes in Q&AMP;As and essays, Dr. B.
guides readers through a child's development, from teething to the
teen years.
</P>
<P>
   Dr. Brazelton is truly an American institution: Professor
Emeritus at Harvard. Author of over two dozen books on child-care
development and pediatrics. Tireless champion of families and
children.
</P>
<P>
   To acquaint you with his child-care beliefs, The New York Times
Syndicate would like to send you a FREE COPY of Dr. Brazelton's
best-selling classic, ``Touchpoints,'' in which he anticipates and
answers all the questions and concerns parents have about their
children's behavior, feelings and development.
