   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-MUDGE (Boston) _ Even though some doctors feel he erred in
diagnosing Reggie Lewis' heart ailment, many medical observers
empathize with Dr. Gilbert Mudge as he defends himself against
malpractice claims. By Karen Hsu. 1280 words.
</P>
<P>
   REOPENED-DIVORCE (Boston) _ Kenan Sahin thought his divorce was
a done deal in 1996. Then he sold his company for $1.48 billion and
the former Mrs. Sahin went back to the lawyers. By Ellen O'Brien.
1270 words. (a and f coding)
</P>
<P>
   SAME-SEX-MARRY (Boston) _ Masschusetts is about to consider a
bill that would deprive legal status to same-sex couples united in
civil marriages. By Tasha Robertson and Diego Ribadeneira. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   SMITH-BLACKS (Northampton, Mass.) _ As colleges struggle to
attain diversity, the black women of Smith's Class of '74 convened
for their 25th reunion and talked about what made diversity work
then. By Kate Zernike. 1700 words. PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   CLASS-OF-99 (Undated) _ They came of age in robust economic
times and many have been given whatever they want. As a result, the
Class of 1999 is about enter the job market with a skewed view of
life. By Matt Brelis. 1250 words.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL-JOURNAL (Chapel Hill, N.C.) _ Honoring Civl War dead in
the South is a truly sad process, as befits a lost cause. By
Michael Kenney.
