<HEADLINE>
BENING GIVES A GREAT PERFORMANCE IN ``IN DREAMS'' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW RELEASES: ``In Dreams'' _ Neil Jordan's haunting film didn't
do well at the box office, but intelligent filmgoers should snap it
up immediately on video. Annette Bening gives a great performance
as an institutionalized career woman in this unconventional horror
movie.
</P>
<P>
   ``Rowing with the Wind'' _ Hugh Grant and Elizabeth Hurley, as
Lord Byron and Claire Clarmont, give this English import a tabloid
buzz. But director Gonzalo Suarez's take on the Percy Bysshe
Shelley-Lord Byron-Mary Shelley literary triangle is tragically
amusing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Bent'' _ Martin Sherman's play about the persecution of gays
in Nazi Germany doesn't make a smooth transition to film. Director
Sean Mathias handles the visuals in a bulky, inconsistent style.
Except for Mike Jagger's outrageous performance as a transvestite,
this one can stay on the shelves.
</P>
<P>
   ``The Cruise'' _ The Gray Line tours usually give tourists a
quick rundown on New York's best-known locations _ the Statue of
Liberty, the Empire State Building, and the Fulton Fish Market. Not
this guy. The star of this wacky documentary heads straight for
Greenwich Village with tales of Henry James and Walt Whitman. It's
a wilder ride than Mr. Toad's.
</P>
<P>
   ``Shadow of Doubt'' _ Randal Kleiser of ``Grease'' and ``Blue
Lagoon'' fame directs this thriller with confidence, if not
inspiration. Melanie Griffith stars with Tom Berenger and the late
Wade Dominguez.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: May 25: ``Saving Private Ryan,'' ``Gloria,''
``Alice in Wonderland,'' ``Horatio Hornblower,'' ``The Aviator's
Wife,'' ``The Marquise of O,'' ``Forbidden Fruit,'' ``Wrestlemania
XV,'' ``Hellcab.'' June 1: ``Berenstain Bears'' (three new
episodes), ``The Base,'' ``Gunshy.'' June 8: ``From the Earth to
the Moon,'' ``Treehouse Hostage,'' ``Psycho'' (remake), ``Gods and
Monsters,'' ``Before Stonewall,'' ``After Stonewall,'' ``Last
Rites.'' June 15: ``Little Voice,'' ``The World Within,'' ``Enemy
of the State,'' ``The Faculty,'' ``Facade,'' ``The Patriot.'' June
22: ``Waking Ned Devine,'' ``Patch Adams,'' ``A Simple Plan,''
``Rushmore,'' ``Wishful Thinking,'' ``Sweethearts,'' ``The Life of
Birds,'' ``Storm of the Century.'' June 29: ``The Thin Red Line,''
``Varsity Blues,'' ``Lansky.'' July 6: ``The King and I''
(animated), ``The Red and the White.'' July 13: ``Life Is
Beautiful,'' ``A Civil Action,'' ``She's All That.'' July 20:
``Down in the Delta,'' ``Telling You,'' ``Mercenary 2: Thick and
Thin.''
</P>
</TEXT>
