estimate of 80 cents a share. By Lawrence M. Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   HOLLAND-CASE (Chicago) _ What New Holland's deal for Case means
for the farm equipment industry. By David Barboza.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Shanghai) _ While China officially remains
committed to trying to join the WTO. Chinese economists say that
apparent divisions in the nation's leadership are likely to further
stiffen Beijing's negotiating position and make agreement difficult
to achieve in the coming months. By Seth Faison.
</P>
<P>
   PHILIPPINES-AIRLINES (Hong Kong) _ The Philippines government
gives financier Lucio Tan an ultimatum over the Philippines
Airlines, which is again teetering on the brink. By Mark Landler.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-OIL (Moscow) _ Lukoil Holding, Russia's largest oil
producer, says it will take over another oil producer through a
share swap. By Neela Banerjee.
</P>
<P>
   AMAZON-DISCOUNT (Undated) _ Amazon.com plans to offer 50 percent
discounts on books that appear on the New York Times best-seller
list. By Doreen Carvajal.
</P>
<P>
   DOW-REUTERS (Undated) _ Dow Jones and Reuters Group say they
will combine interactive business services to tap into each other's
