1997 measure, which would have granted the state's newcomers lower
welfare benefits than those received by residents who have lived
there longer. The 7-2 decision, which could affect 14 other states,
says the limit on benefits for new residents violates their
constitutional right to travel. By MARK HELM. (Already filed, will
update.)
