notoriously prone to boom-bust cycles.
</P>
<P>
   Australia sells about 60 percent of its exports to Asia, many of
them commodities that are always vulnerable to recession in the
region.
</P>
<P>
   But Australia's day of reckoning has never arrived. Instead,
with a growth rate of more than 4 percent over the past year, its
