<HEADLINE>
HOW TO TELL A WOOKIEE FROM A WATTO
</HEADLINE>
 (EDS: Accompanied by STARWARS-HYPE, STARWARS-TV, STARWARS-BOOK) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVE FERMAN 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   _ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   CHARACTERS:
</P>
<P>
   _ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ANAKIN SKYWALKER
</P>
<P>
   (Jake Lloyd)
</P>
<P>
   Slave boy who wants to be a Jedi knight. Grows up to be Darth
Vader.
</P>
<P>
   QUI-GON JINN
</P>
<P>
   (Liam Neeson)
</P>
<P>
   Jedi master, mentor to the young Obi-Wan Kenobi.
</P>
<P>
   OBI-WAN KENOBI
</P>
<P>
   (Ewan McGregor)
</P>
<P>
   Jedi apprentice, mentored by Qui-Gon Jinn. Becomes a Jedi knight
and Anakin's mentor.
</P>
<P>
   QUEEN AMIDALA
</P>
<P>
   (Natalie Portman)
</P>
<P>
   Teen ruler of the peaceful planet Naboo.
</P>
<P>
   DARTH MAUL
</P>
<P>
   (Ray Park)
</P>
<P>
   Devilish dark Lord of the Sith. Apprentice to Darth Sidious.
</P>
<P>
   _ &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Long ago, in a galaxy far, far away, there were so many
characters to keep track of.
</P>
<P>
   The first three episodes of ``Star Wars'' made household names
out of Luke, Han, Princess Leia, Yoda and more, and all three films
had what director George Lucas calls ``arcs,'' intermingled plots
with intermingled characters.
</P>
<P>
   The fourth installment, ``Star Wars: Episode I _ The Phantom
Menace,'' has several more. Some of the characters from the first
three films return, some don't. Several others (most notably
serious bad guy Darth Maul) are new to the ``Star Wars'' universe,
which is about to become more crowded.
</P>
<P>
   Here is a list of who's who, then and now.
</P>
<P>
   THEN &QC;
</P>
<P>
   LUKE SKYWALKER (Mark Hamill): Son of Anakin and Amidala
Skywalker and all-around hero.
</P>
<P>
   HAN SOLO (Harrison Ford): Corellian smuggler, friend of Luke and
Obi-Wan, and Princess Leia's sweetie.
</P>
<P>
   PRINCESS LEIA ORGANA (Carrie Fisher): Luke's twin and leader of
the New Republic.
</P>
<P>
   YODA (Frank Oz): Infinitely wise leader of the Jedi Council and
Luke's mentor. Has best line in the entire series: ``There is no
try _ only do.''
</P>
<P>
   CHEWBACCA (Peter Mayhew): Wookiee, Han Solo's pal, and pilot of
the Millennium Falcon.
</P>
<P>
   OBI-WAN KENOBI (Alec Guinness): Jedi Master. Mentors Luke and
Anakin.
</P>
<P>
   DARTH VADER (voice of James Earl Jones): A very bad little
doggy: Anakin Skywalker, all grown up, half-human and half-machine,
horribly scarred, and evil as a cornered snake.
</P>
<P>
   JABBA THE HUT (Himself): Mountainous bad guy and criminal from
the planet Klatooine; issues contract on Han Solo.
</P>
<P>
   BOBA FETT (Jeremy Bulloch): Bounty hunter; takes Han Solo's
frozen body to Jabba the Hut.
</P>
<P>
   R2-D2 (Kenny Baker): Luke Skywalker's loyal astromech droid and
pal of C-3P0.
</P>
<P>
   C-3PO (Anthony Daniels): Fussy, smart protocol droid with an
English accent.
</P>
<P>
   LANDO CALRISSIAN (Billy Dee Williams): Owner of Cloud City and
friend of Han Solo. Bows to pressure and sells out Solo to Boba
Fett.
</P>
<P>
   WEDGE ANTILLES (Denis Lawson): ``Red Two,'' the X-Wing Red
Leader. Luke's pal. Lawson, incidentally, is Ewan McGregor's uncle.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   NOW &QC;
</P>
<P>
   DARTH SIDIOUS (Ian McDiarmid): The hooded, evil Sith Lord who
mentors Maul.
</P>
<P>
   JAR JAR BINKS (voice of Ahmed Best): A Gungan, (a species of
amphibians on Naboo), he's the cutest of the new computer-generated
creatures. Big floppy basset-hound-like ears. Long neck. Kind eyes
set well above the rest of his, um, head. Buddies with Qui-Gon and
Obi-Wan.
</P>
<P>
   WATTO (Andrew Secombe): Snaggle-toothed Toydarian junk dealer
and owner of the young Anakin Skywalker.
</P>
<P>
   NEBULA (Lewis MacLeod): Master podracer.
</P>
<P>
   MACE WINDU (Samuel L. Jackson): Jedi Council elder, colleague of
Yoda and friend of Obi-Wan Kenobi.
</P>
<P>
   CAPTAIN PANAKA (Hugh Quarshie): Head of Queen Amidala's security
force.
</P>
<P>
   SENATOR PALPATINE (Ian McDiarmid: Chief representative of Naboo.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
