<P>
   AUTO RACING
</P>
<P>
   CAR-BLACKDRIVER _ BRASELTON, Ga. _ Short track driver Preston
Tutt is one of the few black drivers running in a top division, and
he appears to be one of the best. He's rapidly making a name for
himself at Lanier National Speedway in Braselton. Tutt hasn't
visited Victory Lane yet, but he already has won the respect of the
north Georgia natives who race at the 3/8-mile paved oval. The
32-year-old construction worker from Harlem Ga. says he hasn't been
the victim of any racial discrimination. ``I guess that if I went
to the track looking for discrimination I could find it, but I go
there to race,'' he said. (Minter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
WITH PHOTO.
</P>
