   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   GORE-VALUES _ WASHINGTON _ The value-laden campaign themes of
Vice President Al Gore and Texas Gov. George W. Bush have a
familiar ring _ one that former Vice President Dan Quayle sounded
exactly seven years ago today. Quayle returns Wednesday to the same
forum where he delivered his famous ``Murphy Brown'' speech. But
Quayle's family value themes are no laughing matter any more.
(Shepard, Cox News Service) ETA: 5 p.m.
</P>
