   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MALCOLM-DIARY (Undated) _ When Malcolm X was assassinated, a
bloodied, bullet-punctured diary was removed from his body by New
York City police as evidence and never returned to the family. Now
it's at a San Francisco auction house, which hopes it will bring at
least $50,000. His familiy is mystified and angry, and there are
questions about police involvement in its disappearance. By Diego
Ribadeneira. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HOSPITALS-MEDICARE (Washington) _ Cutbacks to hospitals to cover
the cost of Medicare patients are far worse than Congress intended
when it passed a 1997 law, hospital industry says. By Aaron Zitner.
900 words.
</P>
<P>
   CVS-ONLINE (Undated) _ In what may be an industry first, CVS
Corp., the 4,100-store pharmacy chain based in Woonsocket, R.I.,
agrees to pay $30 million for Soma.com of Seattle, one of the first
Internet pharmacies to sell prescription drugs on-line. By Chris
Reidy. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
