<P>
   FOR TUESDAY AMs
</P>
<P>
   Business Day Front Page (coded ``f'')
</P>
<P>
   (Lede story)
</P>
<P>
   USWEST-GLOBAL (Undated) _ In all the analysis of Monday's $37
billion merger of US West Inc., the smallest of the Bell local
phone giants, and Global Crossing Ltd., the international
communications upstart, the most telling commentary may have been
the sound of silence coming from the Federal Communications
Commission. By Seth Schiesel.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Graphic is being sent to NYT graphics clients.
Non-subscribers can make individual purchase by calling (888)
603-1036 or (888) 346-9867.)
</P>
<P>
   (The story is scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   (Center display)
</P>
<P>
   SOCIAL-PHOBIA-DRUGS (Undated) _ Social phobia ranks as the
third-most prevalent psychiatric disorder in the United States
after substance abuse and depression, affecting an estimated 19
million Americans. And just as the pharmaceutical industry has
introduced medicines in recent years to alleviate such common
afflictions as obesity, baldness and sexual impotence, it now sees
a huge market in social anxiety. By Anuradha Raghunathan.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo and graphic are being sent to NYT photo/graphics
