<HEADLINE>
NBA PLAYOFF CAPSULES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICHIE WHITT 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
\Nsubheds:WESTERN
3. Utah Jazz vs. 2. Portland Trail Blazers Season series: Jazz won,
2-1
<TEXT>
<P>
   Jazz scouting report: Utah is 24-4 at the Delta Center,
including an 11-point victory over Portland last month. ... Won two
of three against the Blazers, with the only loss coming in double
overtime at the Rose Garden in February. ... Byron Russell has
become a viable crunch-time option, nailing huge 3-pointers in
Games 4 and 5 against the Kings. ... Utah's half-court execution
has been tremendously effective against Portland's physical,
sometimes over-aggressive defense.
</P>
<P>
   Trail Blazers scouting report: Their main edges are depth and
rest, having swept the Phoenix Suns while Utah struggled to put
away feisty Sacramento in five. ... Their confidence is brimming,
having gotten past the first round for the first time in seven
years. ... They pounded Utah on the backboards in the three
meetings, but allowed the Jazz to shoot 49 percent.
</P>
<P>
   Key matchup: Jazz PF Karl Malone vs. Blazers PF Brian Grant.
Malone didn't have a 30-point game against Sacramento and was at
times badly outplayed by Chris Webber. Grant, who made 23 of his 32
shots against the Suns, has become one of the league's best
finishers around the hoop. In the past, Malone has used Grant's
aggressive defense against him with backdoor cuts and lob passes.
</P>
<P>
   Prediction: Jazz in seven.
\Nsubheds:EASTERN 4. Atlanta Hawks vs. 8. New York Knicks
Season series: Hawks won, 2-1
</P>
<P>
   Hawks scouting report: Somehow beat New York twice in the
regular season despite shooting 34 percent. ... Should get a boost
from the return of PF Alan Henderson from an eye injury. ... Their
stingy defense, anchored by C Dikembe Mutombo, allowed only 73, 80
and 78 points in three games against the Knicks.
</P>
<P>
   Knicks scouting report: They have a huge edge off the bench in G
Latrell Sprewell. The Hawks got only two points from reserves in
their Game-5 victory over Detroit. ... After his Game 5 winner, G
Allan Houston will have his hands full against Atlanta's No. 1
option, Steve Smith.
</P>
<P>
   Key matchup: Hawks C Dikembe Mutombo vs. Knicks C Patrick Ewing.
Given Mutombo's drastically improved low-post moves and Ewing's
aching knees and feet, Atlanta should have a big edge here. As the
Pistons finally figured out, however, Mutombo wilts under
double-team pressure.
</P>
<P>
   Prediction: Knicks in six.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
