<SLUG> BC-DATAGEN-CLARIION-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DATA GENERAL TO EXPAND DISK STORAGE UNIT 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By RONALD ROSENBERG  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Seeking a larger portion of the computer storage market, Data
General Corp. said Monday it will spend about $100 million to add
more than 450 people primarily in sales, technical support and
marketing.
</P>
<P>
   Over the next 18 months, the Westborough, Mass. company will add
about 100 new employees to its Clariion division in Massachusetts
and the balance spread out in US and overseas offices, a company
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
   Of the 450 hires _ the company now employs 4,800 including 1,800
in the Bay State _ more than 250 will be in sales, with the balance
in engineering to assist in the sale of the Clariion product line.
The Clariion division currently has a sales force of 50 people who
sell primarily to companies that repackage the company's disk
storage system and software to reach corporate customers.
</P>
<P>
   In expanding its disk storage division, which last year
accounted for just over $400 million of the company's $1.5 billion
in revenue, Data General hopes to get a leg up on archrival EMC
Corp. of Hopkinton, Mass., the leading supplier of disk storage
systems. Last year EMC had revenue of $4 billion.
</P>
<P>
   ``They're betting they can do better than EMC in this market,''
said William Milton, an analyst at Brown Brothers Harriman. ``It's
a big gamble.''
</P>
<P>
   Part of Data General's product line includes a new technology
called Fibre Channel that uses specialized semiconductor chips with
fiber-optic cables and custom software to dramatically speed the
flow of data among a panoply of refrigerator-sized storage systems
and to computer servers, without impacting local area networks.
</P>
<P>
   The market for Fibre Channel communications is expected to grow
65 percent annually for the next few years, said Ronald L. Skates,
Data General president and chief executive.
</P>
<P>
   EMC does not have a competing Fibre Channel system on the
market.
</P>
<P>
   With a bigger sales force, Data General expects to focus on
major computer providers such as Sun Microsystems Inc., Compaq
Computer Corp., and Hewlett-Packard Co. along with big corporate
customers.
</P>
<P>
   ``This a great opportunity for Data General in a market which
has enormous potential,'' said Skates.
</P>
<P>
   Following up on its sales expansion plans, Data General is
expected to announce Tuesday its strategy on storage systems linked
to create so-called Storage Area Networks. SANs are a new way for
Internet-based computer networks to store information.
</P>
<P>
   Data General shares closed at 12, down 1/4. EMC shares fell 1 to
102 3/4.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
