<HEADLINE>
GIVE UNTIL IT HURTS
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   The latest fund-raising letter from the National Rifle
Association, the first since the Colorado high school shootings,
offers a $10-off coupon toward the $35 annual dues.
</P>
<P>
   ``Time is short,'' writes &UR; Wayne LaPierre &LR; , executive vice
president. ``I am counting on you, as a gun owner and as a
patriotic, law abiding American, to accept your place in the
history of freedom by joining the NRA.''
</P>
<P>
   LaPierre, whose letter is quoted by U.S. News &AMP; World Report,
says that anti-NRA feelings are caused by nothing but propaganda
from the media. ``Instead of doing their homework, and giving the
American people the real facts about guns and crime, the national
media has simply repeated the lies put forth by the gun-ban
lobby.''
</P>
<P>
   P.S. The comments attributed to  &UR; Howard Stern  &LR; in last week's
Personals were actually made by a caller to the show, reported
incorrectly by wire services. Stern's comments, according to
several readers who heard them firsthand, were respectful and
tasteful.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; THE BEST OF BRITAIN &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Prince Philip  &LR; told the Sunday Telegraph that he doesn't keep
up with his former daughter-in-law, the  &UR; Duchess of York &LR; , because
he doesn't ``see much point in it.'' He also said that it's not
been easy being a prince _ ``I had to fit into the institution'' _
and that he values his reputation as a grump. ``Safer not to be too
popular,'' he said. ``You can't fall too far.''
</P>
<P>
   The prince will be putting out the welcome mat, no doubt, for
 &UR; Ken Kesey  &LR; and the Merry Pranksters, who are shipping their bus to
England from Oakland on June 10, meeting up with it in London on
August 6 and thereafter commencing the WheresMerlin tour, &LR; 
throughout England, Wales, Ireland and Scotland. The tour includes
theatrical performances and a search for Merlin, who's supposed to
have some role or other in the millennium.
</P>
<P>
   All this, to be filmed for British television, begins with a Bon
Voyage party on June 4 at the Anon Salon in San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the Mirror of London says that black and white
portraits of  &UR; Edward Windsor &LR;  and  &UR; Sophie Rhys-Jones &LR; , to be used
on a new stamp commemorating their wedding, are ``the cheesiest of
royal pictures yet.'' And in preparation for the wedding, paintings
of the bride's home town _ Brenchley in Kent _ by a dozen
California artists will be exhibited at the Art Center Gallery
Store in San Rafael during June. The show includes works by
 &UR; Christopher Rhys-Jones &LR; , the bride's father.
</P>
<P>
   Finally, in Wexford, Ireland, the county newspaper, Wexford
People, reports that a city council member has called for an
official apology after Mayor &UR; Padge Reck &LR;  called a fellow council
member a scatalogical term that's not fit for printing here but you
wouldn't understand in American English anyway.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BODY LANGUAGE &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ First, there's the tale of the customer who came into the
Vibrant Health store in Mill Valley looking for some
memory-boosting Gingko Biloba but forgot why she was there.
</P>
<P>
   Then, says  &UR; Matt Mosby &LR; , there are the customers who don't quite
recall the proper names of commonly sought-after herbs: ``I'd like
some euthanasia'' indicates a need for echinacea; ``I need
melanoma'' means a hunt for melatonin; and ``Some silly cock,
please'' means the customer, who's always right, wants
oscillococcinum.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Dorothy Feltham &LR;  was lucky enough to be in Nice, France,
recently, but not lucky enough to be at Le Pub Opera on April 1,
when the card that advertised ``Ses Plats Du Jour'' indicated the
special would be pork with ``Pommes Vapeur'' and ``Sauce Viagra.''
</P>
<P>
   _ If your left ear is bigger than your right, or your right
nostril is bigger than your left, you may be at a disadvantage when
it comes to running. A study reported in the International Journal
of Sports Medicine, cited in Muscle and Fitness magazine, found
that people with symmetrical features posted faster running times
on average than those with uneven events &LR;  ones.
</P>
<P>
   _ A survey taken by the Computer Clothing Research Center of
Nottingham Trent University for Marks and Spencer in England has
found that ``Compared with the '50s, nipples are lower than they
used to be,'' said Professor  &UR; Stephen Gray &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   ``One boyfriend always wanted to make love to Verdi's opera `Il
Trovatore.' Our sex session would revolve around two hours of
music. ... After a while, I stoped saying `bravo' and decided to
bail. But I'll never listen to opera the same way again.''
</P>
<P>
   _ Betsy, an accountant, in Glamour magazine.
