<P>
   (NYT22) UNDATED -- May 17, 1999 -- TERRORIST-SUSPECT, 5-17 --
After eight months of secret negotiations in which the U.S.
government sought to win the cooperation of Ali Mohamed, a
suspected chief lieutenant to Osama bin Laden seen in this undated
photo made from a video tape, talks have broken down between the
parties, and federal officials have decided to seek his indictment,
lawyers said on Monday. (New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) JERUSALEM -- May 17, 1999 -- ISRAEL-VOICES, 5-17 --
Supporters of both Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu and his Labor
Party rival Ehud Barak share a street corner opposite a polling
place on Monday. Character issues figured prominently in
conversations with voters on Monday. (Rina Castelnuovo/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
