   (NYT8) NEWTON, Mass. -- May 17, 1999 -- BRUSH-MAN-BOS, 05-17 --
Al Cohen with some sample of his wares. At age 47, Cohen is a
six-day-a-week door-to-door Fuller Brush salesman. ``I'm the last
of a dying breed,'' admits the 30-year sales veteran. ``But I have
a customer base of about 1,000 that I've built up over the years
and I enjoy serving them.'' (Tom Herde/Boston Globe Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT7) NEW YORK -- May 17, 1999 -- SCI-BALLET-PREGNANCY, 5-17 --
Stacey Calvert, a ballerina with the New York City ballet, with her
six month-old daughter Ayla during an exercise session. Looking on
is Calvert's colleague Margaret Tracy with her six month-old son
Avery. This month, both ballerinas had their post-baby debuts, and
the experience made it clear that it is far easier to get in great
shape soon after pregnancy or other disruptive events if one has
been in great shape to begin with. (Andrea Mohin/New York Times
Photo) LITE
