<HEADLINE>
MEXICO MAY ISSUE WARNING ON TRAVELS TO HOUSTON
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY _ Mexican officials say they may issue a travel
advisory about the dangers of visiting Houston, Texas, where three
Mexican citizens have been killed by police officers since 1997,
according to Mexican news reports, which did not name the
officials.
</P>
<P>
   While the United States routinely cautions Americans about the
risks of crime in certain parts of Mexico, Mexico has never issued
a travel advisory about an American city.
</P>
